The paper focuses on image processing and dictionary learning, which are both subfields of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses the issue of compressive sensing (cs.IT) and sparse recovery (cs.SP), which are relevant to the topic of whole-image recovery. The use of subproblems and averaging to handle non-overlapping patches suggests a machine learning approach (cs.LG), and the acceleration of computation using a block proximal-gradient method suggests optimization (cs.MM).
